bib_record.title: The 48Ca(d,p)49Ca reaction across the coulomb barrier.

free_txt: For the angular distributions, four movable detectors
were used to take data simultaneously, while a fifth
detector was fixed at 90 degr. to serve as a monitor.
Dead-time corrections were made for each detector.
Absolute cross sections were obtained by observing the
Rutherford scattering of 2 MeV protons on the targets,
The targets were prepared from Ca3Co enriched to 90% in
48Ca. The pure calcium metal is evaporated onto
backings of formvar plus carbon. The targets (15 -
20 mu-g/cm2 thick) were immediately transferred to the
scattering chamber, but it was impossible to prevent
Error from the graphic bars. The error bars
